Martiale epigram proves that he was not altogether independent or comfortable about this time. (of which the first in our collection was one), having already recited them to large audiences. He continued to write freely during Trajan’s reign, which ended An. 117, when Juvenal was about sixty, and during the early years of Hadrian’s reign, that is, till about nn. 120.
